00:06:02.116 --> 00:06:06.776 A:middle
The first is to direct
people's attention.

00:06:06.776 --> 00:06:09.766 A:middle
To help them become
aware that something

00:06:09.766 --> 00:06:14.016 A:middle
within your app has changed.

00:06:14.426 --> 00:06:18.396 A:middle
Perhaps something behind the
scenes in your app has changed.

00:06:18.426 --> 00:06:19.816 A:middle
You want your users
to understand

00:06:19.816 --> 00:06:22.306 A:middle
that there's something
new that they can explore.

00:06:22.956 --> 00:06:31.276 A:middle
Or perhaps your user has
performed some type of action.

00:06:32.376 --> 00:06:33.636 A:middle
Maybe you are going
to press and hold

00:06:33.636 --> 00:06:34.916 A:middle
on these icons for a little bit.

00:06:36.036 --> 00:06:40.586 A:middle
This animation is communicating
the result of the user's action.

00:06:40.796 --> 00:06:46.066 A:middle
By pressing and holding, I've
changed the state of the app.

00:06:46.336 --> 00:06:48.286 A:middle
So directing attention
can be useful

00:06:48.346 --> 00:06:50.466 A:middle
for both of those scenarios.

00:06:54.256 --> 00:06:59.446 A:middle
The second reason to animate is
to help keep people oriented.

00:06:59.446 --> 00:07:03.666 A:middle
